OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F401A1777114970
OL,3,CVeteran plans to become first triple
OL,4,Camputee to complete London Marathon
OL,6,FAn Army veteran is planning to become
OL,7,Fthe first triple amputee to complete
OL,8,Fthe London Marathon in the hopes of
OL,9,Fshowing others with a disability or
OL,10,Finjury what can be achieved "with the
OL,11,Fright mindset and the right support
OL,12,Fnetwork".
OL,14,FFormer corporal Andy Reid, who lost
OL,15,Fboth legs and his right arm after
OL,16,Fstepping on an improvised explosive
OL,17,Fdevice in Afghanistan in 2009 when on
OL,18,Fpatrol with the 3rd Battalion, the
OL,19,FYorkshire Regiment, expects it will
OL,20,Ftake him 12-13 hours and 80,000 steps
OL,21,Fto complete the 26.2 miles.
OL,26,@rD@]OUtD@HO]
